Give these colors an appropriate name based on their hex value

#00aeef, #F38321", #ffcb05, #f58220, #6ad178, #176922, #f15a22, #eeb024, #00338d, #0066b3, #fffac2

Here are the names for the colors based on their hex value:

* #00aeef: This color is a bright blue and could be called "Cerulean".
* #F38321: This color is a burnt orange and could be called "Tangerine".
* #ffcb05: This color is a vibrant yellow and could be called "Lemon".
* #f58220: This color is a warm orange and could be called "Pumpkin".
* #6ad178: This color is a light green and could be called "Mint".
* #176922: This color is a dark green and could be called "Forest".
* #f15a22: This color is a deep red-orange and could be called "Scarlet".
* #eeb024: This color is a golden yellow and could be called "Marigold".
* #00338d: This color is a navy blue and could be called "Midnight".
* #0066b3: This color is a deep blue and could be called "Royal".
* #fffac2: This color is a pale yellow and could be called "Cream".
